sentences: Barraclough originated in New Mexico before moving to the eastern coast of the United States.
During her career, she released two albums, a self-titled record in 1978 and Hi!
in 1979, both on Grossman's Bearsville Records.
Her 1978 album spawned a 45 single, "Covered Up In Aces."
Barraclough performed "Covered Up In Aces" on The Old Grey Whistle Test during an episode documenting the 1977 Bearsville Picnic in Woodstock, New York.
